    <div class="description">
      <h2>Avril Lavinge</h2>
      <p> 
        Avril Lavigne‚Äôs 2000s fashion redefined pop-punk style with its bold mix of edgy and casual elements. Known for her iconic
         ties over tank tops, baggy cargo pants, studded belts, and layered wristbands, she created a rebellious yet approachable look.
          Her style influenced youth culture, blending skater
         vibes with rock-inspired individuality.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container" style="margin-top: 40px;">
    <img src="sara jessica.jpg" alt="Image 2">
    <div class="description">
      <h2>Sarah Jessica Parker</h2>
      <p>
        Sarah Jessica Parker‚Äôs 2000s fashion embodied elegance and trend-setting glamour, heavily influenced by her role in Sex and 
        the City. Known for bold prints, chic dresses, statement heels, and daring accessories, she combined sophistication
         with experimentation.
         Her fearless style choices shaped early 2000s fashion, making her a global icon of modern femininity.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container" style="margin-top: 40px;">
    <img src="nichple richie.jpg" alt="Image 3">
    <div class="description">
      <h2>Nichole Richie</h2>
      <p>
        Nicole Richie‚Äôs 2000s fashion became synonymous with the boho-chic trend. She embraced oversized sunglasses,
         flowy maxi dresses, layered jewelry, and casual yet glamorous looks. Often styled with loose waves and vintage-inspired pieces,
          her effortless aesthetic defined Hollywood street fashion. Nicole‚Äôs influence made bohemian style mainstream,
         inspiring countless young women worldwide.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

